===Etymology===
;"ruin"
:Possibly a nominal derivation, with *''k-'' prefix, from {{och-l|[[虛]]}} ({{zh-ref|Karlgren, 1958}}, {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), maybe related to {{cog|lus|ko||raised ground; bank; mound}}. Perhaps not related to {{och-l|丘}} "mound, hill" (contra {{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}).

;"market"
:A Yuè (越) dialectal word, which also occurs in some Tai languages such as {{cog|yoy|tr=hɯ<sup>A1</sup>|t=market}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). It also occurs in some Min dialects; {{zh-ref|Kwok (2018)}} reconstructs Proto-Southern Min *''hɯ<sup>1</sup>''.

